# Auto Deploy Workflow

## Frontend (Netlify)
- Build: `npm run build` → outputs `dist/`.
- Deploy: `netlify deploy --prod --dir=dist`.
- Env: `VITE_API_BASE` must point to backend public URL.

## Backend (Railway)
- Project: `appsamurai-dashboard-backend` production env.
- Domain: managed via `railway domain -s appsamurai-dashboard-backend`.
- Env: `CORS_ORIGINS=https://ubiquitous-sherbet-b4f6bf.netlify.app`, `API_KEY`, `DATABASE_PUBLIC_URL`.
- Deploy: from `server/` → `railway up --service appsamurai-dashboard-backend --ci`.

## Commands
```bash
# FE
git add .
git commit -m "Auto-commit: $(date +%Y-%m-%d_%H:%M:%S) - FE update"
git push origin main
npm run build
netlify deploy --prod --dir=dist

# BE (server/)
cd server
npm run build
railway up --service appsamurai-dashboard-backend --ci
```

## Verification
- FE: Open production URL and check UI.
- BE: `curl $VITE_API_BASE/api/health` should be `200 {"status":"ok"}`.

